SIMPLE: teller
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Teller
<hw>Tell"er</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>One who
tells, relates, or communicates; an informer, narrator, or
describer.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>One of four officers of the English Exchequer,
formerly appointed to receive moneys due to the king and to pay moneys
payable by the king.</def> <rj><au>Cowell.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>An employee of a bank who receives money paid in,
and pays money out, and makes records of such transactions.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <def>One who is appointed to count the votes given in a
legislative body, public meeting, assembly, etc.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Tellership</ent>⟦br⟧
